         <abstract>
            <p>La place de la musique dans À la recherche du temps perdu a suscité nombre de commentaires. Le présent propos connecte ces points à un débat interne aux musicologues français. Si certains l'envisage contre toute interpretation subjective, d'autres entendent la recentrer sur deux axes majeurs: 1) le statut d'écrit littéraire 2) révélant l'expérience musicale d'autre part. Or, de récents articles insèrent Proust à ce débat. Il s'agit de comprendre en quoi réactualiser écrivain ayant fait d'un roman un projet esthétique où la question du langage est centrale peut relancer la discussion du lien musique-langage, ici en un rapport où s'adjoint la musicologie, elle-même objet d'une dissension. /// The work À la recherche du temps perdu by Marcel Proust has provoked numerous commentaries which referred to the importance conferred upon music in this novel. In this, interest was pointed either at the music sources, the listening, or the connections between the architecture of the novel and the musical structure of the composer Vinteuil, the character in the novel. This article offers the articulation of those debates which occur within the French musicology which question its objects in the way that some consider it as a science or discipline at intersection of others, which has to return necessarily within sciences called exact and/or humane, opposed to all subjective interpretations; the other try to center again musicologist's activities in two main axes: the status of a writing with a literary aspiration on one side, and a report about musical experience on the other. In this, recent articles were putting Marcel Proust in the focus of a contemporary debate, trying to understand in which way the reactualisation of a writer - who out of one work had made an aesthetical project in which the question of language became central - can renew the discussion about connections between music and language, but this time within a triangular connection in which musicology is added, which by itself is an object of dissention of the same order. /// Djelo U potrazi za izgubljenim vremenom (À la recherche du temps perdu) Marcela Prousta izazvalo je brojne komentare koji su se odnosili na važnost pridanu glazbi u ovome romanu. Pri tome je svejedno jesu li se odnosili na glazbene izvore, slušanje glazbe ili na veze između arhitekture romana i glazbene strukture djela skladatelja Vinteuila, lika u romanu. Ovaj članak ima namjeru artikulirati navedene točke oko interne rasprave u okvirima francuske muzikologije koja ispituje i cilja na svoje predmete tako kao da je neki smatraju znanošću, ili disciplinom na raskrižju mnogih, što se nužno mora vratiti u krilo znanosti zvanih egzaktnima i/ili humanih, protivno svakoj subjektivnoj interpretaciji; drugi pak smatraju da djelatnost muzikologa valja ponovno usredotočiti na dvije glavne osi: pravilo pisanja s književnog gledišta s jedne strane, dok se s druge strane izvještava o glazbenom iskustvu. U vezi s ovime nedavno objavljeni članci ponovno stavljaju Marcela Prousta u žarište suvremene rasprave. Radi se o tome da se shvati po čemu ova reaktualizacija jednoga pisca, koji je od umjetničkog djela napravio estetički projekt u kojemu pitanje jezika ima središnje mjesto, može ponovno pokrenuti raspravu o o vezama između glazbe i jezika, ali u jednom triangularnom odnosu u kojem se pridružuje muzikologija, koja je i sama predmet nesuglasja istoga reda.</p>
         </abstract>
